perspective

  • perspective(X: VectorE3, n: number, f: number, α: number, aspect: number): R3
    • Defined in davinci-eight/diagram/Diagram3D.ts:144

    Perspective transformation projects camera coordinates onto the image space. The near plane corresponds to -1. The far plane corresponds to +1.

    Parameters

    • X: VectorE3

      The coordinates in the camera frame.

    • n: number

      The distance from the camera eye to the near plane onto which X is projected.

    • f: number

      The distance to the far plane.

    • α: number

      The angle subtended at the apex of the pyramid in the vw-plane.

    • aspect: number

      The ratio of the width to the height (width divided by height).

    Returns R3

rotorFromDirectionsE3

  • rotorFromDirectionsE3(a: Vector, b: Vector, B: Bivector, m: Output): void
    • Defined in davinci-eight/math/rotorFromDirectionsE3.ts:28

    Sets this multivector to a rotor representing a rotation from a to b. R = (|b||a| + b a) / sqrt(2 |b||a|(|b||a| + b << a)) If the vectors are anti-parallel, making the plane of rotation ambiguous, the bivector B will be used if specified. Otherwise, returns a random bivector if the vectors are anti-parallel.

    Parameters

    • a: Vector
    • b: Vector
    • B: Bivector
    • m: Output

    Returns void

  • view(X: VectorE3, eye: VectorE3, look: VectorE3, up: VectorE3): R3
    • Defined in davinci-eight/diagram/Diagram3D.ts:108

    View transformation converts world coordinates to camera frame coordinates. We first compute the camera frame (u, v, w, eye), then solve the equation X = x u + y v z n + eye

    Parameters

    • X: VectorE3

      The world vector.

    • eye: VectorE3

      The position of the camera.

    • look: VectorE3

      The point that the camera is aimed at.

    • up: VectorE3

      The approximate up direction.

    Returns R3

    The coordinates in the camera (u, v, w) basis.
